name: arte que me faz chorar
description: the day I saw this esculture from Lygia Clark on MASP (São Paulo museum of art) I cried and felt like home. this is a fragment from the second photo collage page of the zine serie "sou uma casa sem endereço" which portrays the dubious feelings of traveling and coming back home even when there may not be one. brazilian poetry by beatrizporumtriz
